author: Inside Edition
description: Alanna Zabel taught yoga to Rob Reiner's son, Nick, when he was 8 years old and she says the experience was so disturbing, she wrote a children's book about it. The book is called "A Chair in the Air" and it features a boy named Nicky. Zabel says she was devastated when she learned the news that her former student is now charged with his parents' murders. Nick Reiner's struggles are well-documented. Inside Edition spoke to Lin Sternlicht, co-founder of Family Addiction Specialist.
title: Nick Reiner's Former Yoga Instructor Says Experience Was Disturbing

author: Inside Edition
description: Two days after the Brown University shooting, MIT professor Nuno Loureiro was gunned down at his home in Brookline, Massachusetts. The 47-year-old was a renowned professor of nuclear science and engineering. The shooting at Brown, an hour away, targeted the School of Engineering and Physics. Many are wondering if there is a connection between the shootings. Inside Edition spoke with Joseph Scott Morgan, professor of forensics at Jacksonville State University.
title: Is There A Connection Between MIT Professor Murder And Brown University Killings?

author: Inside Edition
description: A school in Indiana honored two of its students for their bravery. It all started a couple weeks earlier at a pool party. Braxtan says he jumped into the pool, not realizing he was jumping into the deep end. When he couldn't get his footing, he started to go under. Then, Clark the birthday boy came to the rescue. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Birthday Boy Saves Friend From Drowning During Pool Party

author: Inside Edition
description: Inside Edition's Alison Hall explains how to wear your jacket hood properly.
title: Are You Wearing The Hood Of Your Winter Jacket All Wrong? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: What would you get if you crossed the movies Wall Street and A Christmas Carol? Something like this, according to the minds of a group of actors in Nashville. The Street Theatre Company is presenting its show entitled "A VHS Christmas Carol." The audience keeps coming back year after year. Now in its 20th season, the company says they do their best to keep things interesting. This year they went all out with the 1980s theme. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Nashville Theatre Group Brings Ebenezer Scrooge Into The 1980s

author: Inside Edition
description: The FBI put out a wanted poster with a $50,000 reward.
title: Manhunt For Brown University Shooter Continues #shorts
